## **Method 1: Browser Console (Recommended)**

1. **Open Browser Developer Tools** (F12)
2. **Go to Console tab**
3. **Connect to WebSocket:**

```javascript
// Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN with actual token from login
const token = 'YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE';
const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:8000/ws/notifications/?token=${token}`);

ws.onopen = () => {
    console.log('âœ… Connected to Jamii Spot notifications');
};

ws.onmessage = (event) => {
    const data = JSON.parse(event.data);
    console.log('ðŸ“© Notification received:', data);

    // Log different notification types
    switch(data.notification_type) {
        case 'friend_request_received':
            console.log(`ðŸ‘‹ Friend request from ${data.data.from_user_username}`);
            break;
        case 'friend_request_accepted':
            console.log(`ðŸŽ‰ ${data.data.new_friend_username} accepted your friend request!`);
            break;
        case 'countrymate_traveling_nearby':
            console.log(`ðŸŒ ${data.data.username} from ${data.data.home_country} is traveling nearby`);
            break;
        case 'location_search_performed':
            console.log(`ðŸ” Discovery search: ${data.message}`);
            break;
        default:
            console.log(`ðŸ“¨ ${data.type}: ${data.message}`);
    }
};

ws.onerror = (error) => console.error('âŒ WebSocket error:', error);
ws.onclose = () => console.log('ðŸ”Œ WebSocket connection closed');
```

## **Method 2: Command Line (wscat)**

```bash
# Install wscat globally
npm install -g wscat

# Connect to WebSocket
wscat -c "ws://localhost:8000/ws/notifications/?token=YOUR_JWT_TOKEN"
```

## **Method 3: Postman WebSocket**

1. Create new **WebSocket Request** in Postman
2. URL: `ws://localhost:8000/ws/notifications/?token=YOUR_JWT_TOKEN`
3. Click **Connect**
4. Monitor messages in real-time

## **Notification Types to Test:**

| Action | Triggers Notification | Recipient |
|--------|----------------------|----------|
| Send friend request | `friend_request_received` | Request recipient |
| Accept friend request | `friend_request_accepted` | Request sender |
| Update travel status | `countrymate_traveling_nearby` | Nearby countrymates |
| Perform discovery search | `location_search_performed` | Searching user |
| Post new story | `friend_new_story` | All friends |
| Story processing complete | `story_processing_complete` | Story creator |

## **Test Sequence:**

1. **Connect Mary to WebSocket** (using mary_token)
2. **Connect John to WebSocket** (using john_token)
3. **Run any API action** (friend request, travel update, etc.)
4. **Observe real-time notifications** in both connections

